    "about": {
        "title": "About",
        "intro": "A developer who grows through <span class='highlight-text-primary'>self-driven projects</span> and turns ideas into <span class='highlight-text-secondary'>real products</span>.",
        "description": "A <span class='highlight-text-primary'>web development-focused</span> mindset; building on both frontend and backend, learning new technologies through <span class='highlight-text-secondary'>hands-on experimentation</span>, and prioritizing <span class='highlight-text-tertiary'>maintainable code</span>.",
        "full": "I have been actively involved in software development for the past few years, mostly improving myself through my own projects. Turning an idea into a working product is the part I enjoy the most.<br/><br/>I mainly work in web development. I have built projects using technologies such as React, Next.js, Node.js, Express, and Laravel, working on both frontend and backend. I also gained experience in data management with MongoDB and PostgreSQL. Additionally, I developed desktop applications using C# and WinForms, and more recently started experimenting with lightweight modern desktop apps using Tauri (Rust).<br/><br/>Depending on the need, I also work with different tools. For example, I have built projects involving media processing using FFmpeg. I enjoy exploring new technologies, and I generally believe the best way to learn something is by using it directly.<br/><br/>In my projects, I don’t consider it enough for something to just “work”; I try to keep things as clean, understandable, and maintainable as possible. When I face a problem, instead of quickly moving on, I prefer to dig into it and understand how it actually works.<br/><br/>My current goal is to work on larger, real-world impactful projects and further improve myself, especially in backend development and system design.",
        "cta": "Read Full Version"
    },
